E.g. in 1 Samuel 4 when Eli falls from his chair and dies the Bible mentions he was obese and afterwards Phinehas' wife names her son Ichabod which means both "the glory has departed", but also can be read as "the fat one fell" or something of the sort. It's very Swartzweldian...
